data.name: Aarogya - Chetna
data.description:
Introducing a powerful application designed to collect survey data related to the nutrition status of rural areas in the Dang and Navsari districts of Gujarat. The application aims to streamline the survey process, making it easier to collect, analyze, and utilize data to develop effective strategies for improving the nutrition status of the local population.

With this application, survey data can be easily collected and uploaded from the field, eliminating the need for paper-based surveys. The application is user-friendly, with an intuitive interface that makes it easy for surveyors to record data accurately and efficiently.

The collected data is then analyzed using powerful analytical tools, enabling researchers and policymakers to gain insights into the nutritional status of the local population. This information can be used to develop targeted interventions and strategies for improving the nutrition status of the local population.

The application is designed to be scalable, making it ideal for use in large-scale surveys. It is also secure and reliable, with robust security features to protect sensitive data.

Overall, this application is an essential tool for researchers, policymakers, and health professionals working to improve the nutrition status of rural areas in the Dang and Navsari districts of Gujarat. By streamlining the survey process and providing powerful analytical tools, the application enables stakeholders to work more efficiently and develop effective strategies for improving the health and well-being of the local population.

data.name: Ni-kshay Setu Revamp
data.description: Introducing "Drive | Ni-kshay Setu | NTEP Migration | AI Revamp": This project represents a comprehensive overhaul of the existing Ni-kshay Setu platform, incorporating cutting-edge AI technology and seamlessly integrating NTEP (National Tuberculosis Elimination Program) data. Building upon the foundation of the old Ni-kshay Setu system, this initiative aims to modernize and enhance its functionality by leveraging artificial intelligence capabilities. Moreover, it facilitates seamless integration with other TB-related applications, such as Manage TB, fostering a unified ecosystem for effective tuberculosis management.
